The Wealdstone Raider's  hit 'Got No Fans' has climbed to No 5 in the UK singles charts, beating One Director, Taylor Swift and Take That.

The YouTube sensation set his target to beat X Factor and become No 1 by Christmas, with all proceeds from the single going to charity. 

Gordon Hill found fame  when he was filmed confronting a rival supporter at a semi-professional football match featuring his beloved Wealdstone, and the clip has more than 5.5million views.

