The 'Got No Fans' song has been backed by QPR defender Rio Ferdinand, with the former England international directly mentioned in the song. Hill ridicules Joey Barton, Piers Morgan and Gemma Collins before singing: 'Rio Ferdinand, I like you, you've got fans.'

Asked about his single by Sky Sports presenter Laure James while he was at the World Darts Championship on Friday, the builder-by-day said: 'It's called The Wealdstone Raider: Got No Fans. Every penny is going to charity.

'Have you bought my single? Buy my single please for charity!' 

